<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Kerberos on Remko's Blog</title><link>https://remkoweijnen.nl/blog/tags/kerberos/</link><description>Recent content in Kerberos on Remko's Blog</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en-us</language><lastBuildDate>Tue, 21 Aug 2012 11:43:35 +0000</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://remkoweijnen.nl/blog/tags/kerberos/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Error 1787 when logging in with domain account</title><link>https://remkoweijnen.nl/blog/2012/08/21/error-1787-when-logging-in-with-domain-account/</link><pubDate>Tue, 21 Aug 2012 11:43:35 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://remkoweijnen.nl/blog/2012/08/21/error-1787-when-logging-in-with-domain-account/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;After joining a new Windows 2008 R2 Server to the domain I could not login to the domain.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;I would get the following error message:&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;a class="glightbox thickbox" href="https://remkoweijnen.nl/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/clip_image001.webp" data-type="image" data-gallery="post-2717"&gt;&lt;img loading="lazy" decoding="async" style="display: inline" title="Error 1787" alt="The security database on the server does not have a computer acocunt for this workstation trust relationship." src="https://remkoweijnen.nl/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/clip_image001_thumb.webp" width="422" height="116" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Additionally the following error was logged in the Eventlog:&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://remkoweijnen.nl/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/image5.webp" class="glightbox thickbox" data-type="image" data-gallery="post-2717"&gt;&lt;img loading="lazy" decoding="async" style="display: inline" title="Event Properties" alt="Event ID 3 | Error 1787 | Error Code 0x7 | KDC_ERR_S_PRINCIPAL_UNKNOWN | A Kerberos Message was received" src="https://remkoweijnen.nl/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/image_thumb5.webp" width="216" height="240" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>